l welfare acts and policies in terms of their treatment of children of color, and it provides best practices for each decision point in the child welfare process and for cultural competency measures and training. The text offers extensive measurement instruments that agencies can use to assess and correct institutional racism. To improve social work education, the book includes several model syllabi for the curriculum, and to deepen the discipline's engagement with the issue of institutional racism, the text concludes with a discussion of future directions for research and policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aChild welfarezUnited States. 0aRace discriminationzUnited States. 0aSocial service and race relationszUnited States. 0aSocial work with African American children. 0aSocial work with minoritieszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aCourtney, Mark E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/harr1504640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231521031423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231521031.jpg  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles